 steps: (1) copyright the software, and(2) offer you this license which gives you legal permission to copy,distribute and/or modify the software.  Also, for each author''s protection and ours, we want to make certainthat everyone understands that there is no warranty for this freesoftware.  If the software is modified by someone else and passed on, wewant its recipients to know that what they have is not the original, sothat any problems introduced by others will not reflect on the originalauthors'' reputations.  Finally, any free program is threatened constantly by softwarepatents.  We wish to avoid the danger that redistributors of a freeprogram will individually obtain patent licenses, in effect making theprogram proprietary.  To prevent this, we have made it clear that anypatent must be licensed for everyone''s free use or not licensed at all.  The precise terms and conditions for copying, distribution andmodification follow.INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (23, ' Actions    Dieses Modul stallt eine Reihe von Action-Klassen zur Verfügung die in Projekt-Views verwendet werden können.                  getArticle          Beschreibung: Füllt ein Array mit den Daten eines Artikels                     Syntax:               $this->model->action(''article'', ''getArticle'',                      array(''id_article'' => integer,                            ''result''     => & array(),                            ''pubdate''    => array(''>|=| array(''title'',''overtitle'',                                                  ''subtitle'',''header'',                                                  ''description'',''body'',                                                  ''ps'',''pubdate'',                                                  ''articledate'',''modifydate'',                                                  ''logo'',''media_folder'') ));       getNodeArticles                 Beschreibung: Füllt ein Array mit den Daten von Artikeln die sich unterhalb eines Navigationsknoten befinden               Syntax:          $this->model->action(''article'', ''getNodeArticles'',                     array(''id_node'' => integer,                           ''result''  => & array,                           ''status''  => array(''>|=| array(''>|=| array(''rank|title|                                              articledate|pubdate|modifydate                                              overtitle|subtitle'',                                               ''asc|desc''),  // optional                           ''fields''  => array(''title'',''overtitle'',                                               ''subtitle'',''header'',                                               ''description'',''body'',                                               ''ps'',''pubdate'',                                               ''articledate'',''modifydate'',                                               ''logo'',''media_folder'') ));           search    Beschreibung: Füllt ein Array mit den Daten von Artikeln die einem Suchkriterium entsprechen              Syntax:        $this->model->action(''article'', ''search'',                     array(''result''  => & array,                           ''search''  => string,   // search string                           ''status''  => array( ''>|=| array( ''>|=| array(''>|=| array(''rank|title|                                              articledate|pubdate|modifydate                                              overtitle|subtitle'',                                               ''asc|desc''),  // optional                           ''fields''  => array(''title'',''overtitle'',''id_node'',                                              ''subtitle'',''header'',                                              ''description'',''body'',                                              ''ps'',''pubdate'',                                              ''articledate'',''modifydate'',                                              ''logo'',''media_folder'') )); pager          Beschreibung: Erstellt eine Zeichenkette die Paginationlinks enthält                     Syntax: $this->model->action(''article'',''pager'',                       array(''result''     => & array,                            ''id_node''    => integer,                            ''search''     => string, // search string                            ''status''     => array(''>|=| array(''>|=| array(''>|=| integer,                            ''numPage''    => integer,                            ''delta''      => integer,                            ''url''        => string,                            ''var_prefix'' => string,                            ''css_class''  => string));     getStatus            Beschreibung: Gibt den Status eines Artikels und den Status des Artikel zugeörigen Knotens.  $result[''nodeStatus'']  $result[''articleStatus'']                       Syntax:   $model->action(''article'',''getStatus'',                 array(''id_article'' => int,                      ''result''     => & array));    getKeywordIds            Beschreibung: Gibt alle SchlüsselwortID''s zurück die mit einem ArticleID verknüpft sind                       Syntax:    $model->action(''article'', ''getKeywordIds'',                 array(''result''     => &$array(),                       ''id_article'' => int,                       ''key_status'' => array(''>|=|action(''article'',''fromKeyword'',                 array(''id_key_list'' => array( int, int,..,..,..),                       ''result''      => & array,                       ''status''      => array(''>|=| array(''>|=| array(''>|=| array( integers ), // exclude id_articles''s optional                       ''order''   => array(''rank|title|                                           articledate|pubdate|                                           overtitle|subtitle'', ''asc|desc''), // optional                       ''disable_sql_cache'' => TRUE,  // optional                        ''fields   => array(''id_node'',''id_article'',''status'',''rank'',                                          ''activedate'',''inactivedate'',''pubdate'',                                          ''lang'',''title'',''overtitle'',                                          ''subtitle'',''header'',''description'',                                          ''body'',''ps'',''fulltextbody'',                                          ''format'',''media_folder'') ));  ', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (25, ' Public Projects Views and Templates    You will find in the root folders /templates_smart and /views_smart all public views and templates. It''s an example of a project. You should insert the example content during the setup to check out how every thing works together. Based on this example you can adapt the views and templates to your own project conception. In this case you should store your project files in new folders; Ex.: /views_myproject and /templates_myproject, to prevent overwriting your modified files during the next framework update.        Usually every view class has a corresponding template file. The following views and templates are installed by default:  ViewArticle.php - tpl.article.php - This view fetch the demanded article data, assign template variables with this data and loads the corresponding template which outputs the article data.ViewError.php - tpl.error.php - Depending on the configuration settings this view output error messages.ViewHeader.php - tpl.header.php - This view build the output for every page header. ViewIndex.php - tpl.index.php - This view is responsible for the entry page.ViewLogout.php - Do some logout stuff. A logout link only appears in the left navigation bar if the webvisitor has previously login into the admin area. This view dont need any template.  ViewMainNavigation.php - tpl.mainNavigation.php - This view build the main navigation links that appears on the left side of every pageViewNode.php - tpl.node.php - This view fetch the demanded navigation node, articles of this node and links of this node. ViewPicture.php - tpl.picture.php - Show a picture in whole size.ViewSearch.php - tpl.search.php - Show the articles that match a search string   ViewSimpleNode.php - tpl.simpleNode.php - Show a simple navigation node that has no subnodes or articles, links..... ViewSitemap.php - tpl.sitemap.php - Show the whole navigation node tree with articles.   ', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (28, ' The Controller    The controller is the first entry point of the framework that handles requests. It is responsible for that every thing is going on the right way. Depending of its conception the controller execute the following operations:      Send a broadcast init action to all modules   Build some base instance. Amongs others an instance of the model class   Determine the workflow in view classes. Means which methode is executed when. If necessairy build an template instance and renders a template       You can build different controllers with different conceptions. At this time there are 3 controller types available:     Public Web Controller - index.php - It handles the request for a public web page Admin Web Controller - admin.php - It handles the request for the admin web interface CLI Controller - cli.php - This controller handles command line jobsXML_RPC Controller - rpcserver.php - This controller handles remote procedure calls      The Cli Controller      With this controller it is also possible to build complex shell applications as it is the case with unix bash. Through cli.php you can call a specific view. You can call under *nix the example cli View in /views_cli/ViewCliTest.php as follows:       /usr/bin/php ./cli.php -v cliTest [ -f id_node title ] [ -idn 0 ]OR/usr/bin/php ./cli.php --view cliTest [ --fields id_node title ] [ --id_node 0 ]      A Cli view works the same way as the other views except that:      Caching is disabled    No template is rendered There is no append filter methode  Smart3 uses Console_Getargs as command line parser. The XML_RPC Controller     The file rpcserver.php in the root folder is a server which handles xml rpc requests.  RPC is a spec and a set of implementations that allow software running on disparate operating systems, running in different environments to make procedure calls over the Internet.        Smart3 uses the PEAR XML RPC library. You can find the views in the /views_rpcserver folder. Currently there is only one view to test. With this view it is possible to fetch the latest modified or published artikles from a website. You can test the server with the Rpc-Client in /tests/XmlRpcClient.php.   Notice:    The cli and the rpc controllers are yet experimental. It laks of experience with such implementations. But it show you of what is possible in Smart3.  ', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (29, ' Change Log    0.2.6b------- update to TinyMce 2.0.4- added bolg features in article module.  Web users can add comments to articles.&nbsp;0.2.5b------- update to TinyMce 2.0.3- added GD check in setup module- added TinyMce cache- added rss builder action- added ajax server and usage examples (experimental)- added Each article can be assigned with an individual view 0.2.4b------- upgrade to Tinymce 2.0.1- auto public view detection related to articles0.2.3b--------- fixed self reference of nodes and keywords- fixed expired session time settings- fixed small file upload bug- added session expire time in options 0.2.2a------- added keyword module- added keyword features in modules: misc,article,navigation and link- added separated public view and template to show extern links0.2.1a------- in modules &quot;navigation&quot; and &quot;article&quot; you can now set content to protect,  means only registered user have access to.- added C L I (command line interface) controller to build shell applications:   You can find in the root folder the  cli.php controller and the related views in /views_cli as an example  of how to use it.  Example: /bin/php cli.php --view cliTest  As with other controllers, you can use all actions from within cli views  and thus execute complex shell operations.- added rpcserver.php (XML_RPC Server) controller and related views in /views_rpcserver.- added /tests/XmlRpcClient.php. 0.2.0.9a -------- - fixed some nasty warnings under php version 5.0.5 - fixed sql language encoding bug - added article select with pubdate option - added ActionNavigationGetNodeStatus.php action class - modified public error template 0.2.0.8a -------- - fixed small error reporting bug in error handler - added Smarty template engine support. Now you have the   choice between php and Smarty as template engine. 0.2.0.7a -------- - fixed small setup bug - minor fixes 0.2.0.6a -------- - fixed bug in misc module (only on *nix) - added javacript compression for tinymce editor - fixed some links in the doc - fixed small error log bug 0.2.0.5a -------- - fixed image bug in article,navigation and misc module - added admin view folder select in configuration array.   It&#39;s now possible to develop more than one admin view   and its templates. Means switching between multiple   admin layouts. - added support of the mysql client extension.   It supports now mysql and mysqli.  0.2.0.4a -------- - enhanced the article module - added pager classes - minor changes - fixed a few bugs 0.2.0.3a -------- - added article module - added article search public view. - fixed a few bugs  0.2.0.2a -------- - added simple link module - added sending system messages by email. see: my_config_dist.php. - added disallowed upload files in options - fixed modules data dir handling 0.2.0.1a -------- - it is possible to insert sample content on the setup page. 0.2a ---- - Initial release  ', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (30, ' Features    Very simple implementation of the ModelViewController patternEach view can have its own authentication mechanism, prepended filters, appened filters and template render engine type.Loose coupling between the view and the model (module actions)   View cachingDifferent controller types support (Web, Cli, RpcServer, AjaxServer)FastModerated memory  consumtion Module supportPlug&amp;Play of entier modules and its action classesRapide application development  ', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (31, ' Support    For questions, suggestions and critics you should use the Project forum (english, german or french): http://forum.smart3.org   If you need professional support, mailto:   Project leader: Armand Turpel framework@smart3.org  ', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `smart_article_index` VALUES (32, ' Download    You can download the current version at Berlios, where you also can find the Smart3 Subversion repository, or at  Sourceforge.Download Smart3 from BerliosDownload Smart3 from Sourceforge  The core Framework requires php5. The delivered modules require MySql 4.1The size of the whole package is about 7mb. But the most space (3mb) is used by TinyMCE and some Pear packages. The core framework without the modules is about 50kb. Smart3 is developed under the Subversion version control. You can browse the repository here.For reporting bugs, suggestions and questions please use the Smart3 forum.   ', '', '', '');
